# Festag — no mobile auth container scroll

On **mobile** (≤768px), auth entry and auth chrome containers must **never** be finger-scrollable.

## Surfaces

- `/enter` (Client / Developer chooser + video)
- `/login`, `/register` (`.al-root` / `.al-mobile-sheet` / `.al-sheet-body` / `.al-main`)
- Dev login / onboarding auth sheets that share the same mobile chrome

## Do

- Keep `overflow: hidden` on the mobile auth shell (no rubber-band / drag scroll)
- Fit idle content in the viewport with layout and type scale
- Use the **standard mobile keyboard** behavior: `interactiveWidget: 'resizes-content'` so the viewport shrinks and the focused field sits above the keyboard

## Do not

- `overflow-y: auto` / `scroll` on `.al-main`, `.al-sheet-body`, `.al-mobile-sheet`, `.ae-root` for idle browsing
- `scrollIntoView` hacks or custom keyboard insets to fake field visibility
- `interactiveWidget: 'overlays-content'` on auth — that covers the email field with the keyboard
- Reintroduce finger-scroll “just for short phones” — shorten UI instead

When touching mobile auth layout, verify the sheet cannot be dragged/scrolled by the user, while email focus still uses the normal OS keyboard resize.
